-- An nr function for Linear-or-affine.
--
-- The value of nr¬†p¬†рЭЯШ¬†z¬†s¬†n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†рЭЯЩ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls, and the
--   argument is used exactly once in the successor case (excluding
--   erased uses):
--
--     f zero    = f_z
--     f (suc m) = f_s m
--
--   Let us use n¬†+¬†z for the zero case, and n¬†+¬†s for the successor
--   case: the result is a conservative approximation of these two
--   values (their meet).
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†рЭЯШ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive
--   calls, and the argument is not used (in non-erased positions) in
--   the successor case:
--
--     f zero    = f_z
--     f (suc m) = f_s
--
--   Let us again use n¬†+¬†z for the zero case. For the successor case
--   we use вЙ§рЭЯЩ¬†¬Ј¬†n¬†+¬†s: the argument is not used linearly in the
--   successor case, because it is not used at all, so if n is рЭЯЩ, then
--   the result should be at most вЙ§рЭЯЩ (not рЭЯЩ, because the function is
--   not linear, and not рЭЯШ, because that would amount to an erased
--   match on a natural number).
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†вЙ§рЭЯЩ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls, and
--   the argument is used at most once in the successor case
--   (excluding erased uses). Let us again use n¬†+¬†z for the zero
--   case, and вЙ§рЭЯЩ¬†¬Ј¬†n¬†+¬†s for the successor case.
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†вЙ§ѕЙ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls. In the
--   successor case the argument is used an unlimited number of times,
--   so we use вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†n¬†+¬†s. In the zero case we use n¬†+¬†z, as before.
--
-- All of these cases can be expressed in the following way (note that
-- рЭЯЩ¬†вИІ¬†рЭЯШ and рЭЯЩ¬†вИІ¬†вЙ§рЭЯЩ are both equal to вЙ§рЭЯЩ):
--
--   nr p рЭЯШ z s n = ((рЭЯЩ вИІ p) ¬Ј n + s) вИІ (n + z)
--
-- The value of nr¬†p¬†рЭЯЩ¬†z¬†s¬†n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†рЭЯШ, then we have linear recursion: the argument is used
--   linearly (n), the successor case can occur an unlimited number of
--   times (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†s), and the zero case occurs once (z).
--
-- * If p is рЭЯЩ, вЙ§рЭЯЩ or¬†вЙ§ѕЙ, then there is recursion (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†s), the
--   argument can be used in each recursive call (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†n), and the
--   zero case occurs once (z).
--
-- We get the following definition:
--
--   nr p рЭЯЩ z s n = (рЭЯЩ + p) ¬Ј n + вЙ§ѕЙ ¬Ј s + z
--
-- The value of nr¬†p¬†вЙ§рЭЯЩ¬†z¬†s¬†n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†рЭЯШ, then we have affine recursion: the argument is used
--   affinely (вЙ§рЭЯЩ¬†¬Ј¬†n), the successor case can occur an unlimited
--   number of times (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†s), and the zero case occurs at most once
--   (вЙ§рЭЯЩ¬†¬Ј¬†z).
--
-- * If p is рЭЯЩ, вЙ§рЭЯЩ or¬†вЙ§ѕЙ, then there is recursion (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†s), the
--   argument can be used in each recursive call (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†n), and the
--   zero case occurs at most once (вЙ§рЭЯЩ¬†¬Ј¬†z).
--
-- We get the following definition:
--
--   nr p рЭЯЩ z s n = (вЙ§рЭЯЩ + p) ¬Ј n + вЙ§ѕЙ ¬Ј s + вЙ§рЭЯЩ ¬Ј z
--
-- Finally we use the following definition for nr¬†p¬†вЙ§ѕЙ¬†z¬†s¬†n:
--
--   nr _ вЙ§ѕЙ z s n = вЙ§ѕЙ ¬Ј (n + s + z)
--
-- There is recursion (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†s), in the successor case there can be
-- multiple recursive calls (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†n), and the zero case can occur
-- multiple times (вЙ§ѕЙ¬†¬Ј¬†z).

nr :
  Linear-or-affine вЖТ Linear-or-affine вЖТ
  Linear-or-affine вЖТ Linear-or-affine вЖТ Linear-or-affine вЖТ
  Linear-or-affine
nr p рЭЯШ  z s n = ((рЭЯЩ вИІ p) ¬Ј n + s) вИІ (n + z)
nr p рЭЯЩ  z s n = (рЭЯЩ  + p) ¬Ј n + вЙ§ѕЙ ¬Ј s +      z
nr p вЙ§рЭЯЩ z s n = (вЙ§рЭЯЩ + p) ¬Ј n + вЙ§ѕЙ ¬Ј s + вЙ§рЭЯЩ ¬Ј z
nr _ вЙ§ѕЙ z s n = вЙ§ѕЙ ¬Ј (n + s + z)

